title: truly changed my life
content: it all started june 26th 2014, the day i met marcus young. as soon as we saw each other that night, we fell in love. we went on almost daily dates after this, and eventually he asked to get married, and even though our wedding had to be postponed because i couldn‚Äôt find a dress, i never felt happier. flash forward to december 18th, 2023 at exactly 11:34 pm, i got a notification from youtube. it was to watch ‚Äúteapot nine‚Äù. i did not know this yet, but this video would change my life. on january 3rd 2024, when i had came home from work, i heard the news that marcus only had 98 days left to live. me and my children cried alot that day, and those 98 days went very fast, and soon marcus only had 3 days left to live. i watched teapot nine that day in a attempt to think about something else, and i did! april 8th 2024 was not too bad after watching the lunar eclipse and the nine teapots. august of that year, i had met tom. he ended up cheating on me with his guitar. i meet sam? his dad disapproves of me. but after watching teapot nine again, i met coiny! my newer husband and father to my 7 children, and he was the best way to move on from marcus. this app truly changed my life and i would recommend it to anyone reading this review!

title: Youtube promotes scams, gambling and porn
content:
I love the creators that are on this platform, they make so much incredible content that we can access for free. But this is completely undermined by the fact that the platform punishes them for things they are completely in their rights to do (fair use). Meanwhile the platform has no standard when it comes to the advertisers they allow! I have seen medical scams, financial scams, gambling ads, political extremism, and even hardcore pornography (with AI filters) advertised over and over. I report it for clearly violating the ‚Äústandards‚Äù youtube claims to have but it is ignored and nothing is done. It feels like this company is asleep at the wheel and allows abuse of every system they have. This isn‚Äôt even mentioning some of the UX problems that exist, but at this point that is secondary. If Youtube didn‚Äôt already dominate the market it wouldn‚Äôt make sense to continue using the platform. There will be no change and I can‚Äôt wait for this site to go quietly into the darkness as new, better video hosts inevitably do better. 

I can‚Äôt say anyone is safe on this platform and it will not change anything on its own‚Ä¶ DO BETTER!

author: Bertram11
title: Decent functionality, horrible policies
content: This app is pretty good at remembering where you left off, and it deals with the internet signal going in and out OK. It can get confused and wait forever to load a video even when the Internet has come back, so you have to refresh the app sometimes. YouTube policies are a blight for many reasons. For example the algorithm necessitates that creators to use all caps click bait headlines with provocative words to get any chance of an audience. So you will be embarrassed if you open your YouTube app around your parents and they think you will be wasting your time on slop. The policies are horrible to creators, for example music teachers will get their videos taken down and demonetized if they teach music that is copyrighted. In that way it partly is causing all the good old music to disappear. Even if a car drives by with its radio on the entire video could be taken down and all of the creator‚Äôs work gone. YouTube elevates videos with salacious or meaningless drivel, and carefully selects out videos with deep or difficult subjects. Somehow people still make meaningful content that is not taken down‚Äî or through their great effort they get it put back up. This is at a loss to themselves since demonetizing a new video ruins its chance to make money for the creator. Overall, YouTube on Premium is good enough to be my primary source of media, as I get all news, independent news, podcasts, entertainment, comedy, music, and science on the app.

author: Kaiser S√∂≈∫ƒçe
title: 17 yrs later: Suddenly YT demands photo ID and/or CC
content:
I created my YT account in 2008, over 17 years ago, and have been using it ever since. Suddenly, now, Nov 2025, they age-gate my acct (and millions of others) into mandatory kids mode ‚Äî claiming their AI has determined that my acct use and I appear to match the pattern of someone under 18.
‚Ä¶Two things:
(1) I watch news, politics, philosophy, science, college lectures, and technical instructional vids. Stuff that would bore a child to tears.
(2) If I were under 18, my account age itself would mean that I ‚Äîmore than 17 years ago‚Äî would‚Äôve signed up for Gmail, linked that to my YT user profile, and begin using it all AS A 9-MONTH OLD INFANT.
In order to unlock my account from gated kids-mode, they demand photo ID and/or credit card info.
Thanks, but no thanks, Big Brother.
